{{DISPLAYTITLE:VALUE_MAX}}{{TAGDEF|VALUE_MAX|[real array]}}

Description: {{TAG|VALUE_MAX}} sets the upper limits for the monitoring of geometric parameters (in case VASP was compiled with [[Precompiler options#-Dtbdyn|-Dtbdyn]]).
----
For {{TAG|MDALGO}}=1 {{!}} 2, the geometric parameters defined in the {{FILE|ICONST}} file may be monitored without being subjected to a constraint or bias potential (<tt>STATUS=7</tt> in the {{FILE|ICONST}}-file).

If all values of monitored parameters defined in the {{FILE|ICONST}} file (<tt>STATUS=7</tt>) are smaller than {{TAG|VALUE_MIN}} or larger than {{TAG|VALUE_MAX}}, the simulation terminates.

Upper limits for monitored coordinates, must be supplied for each geometric parameter in the {{FILE|ICONST}} file with <tt>STATUS=7</tt>.

